# Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #xxx

## Problem summary

### Remove the memory of the brpc Closure from the query
- In data stream sender, brpc client serialize `Request` memory in `transmit_block()`, release in `closure->cntl.Reset()`, and remove them from query mem tracker.
```
Status VDataStreamSender::Channel::send_block(PBlock* block, bool eos) {
    SCOPED_TIMER(_parent->_brpc_send_timer);
    if (_closure == nullptr) {
        _closure = new RefCountClosure<PTransmitDataResult>();
        _closure->ref();
    } else {
        RETURN_IF_ERROR(_wait_last_brpc());
        SCOPED_SWITCH_THREAD_MEM_TRACKER_LIMITER(ExecEnv::GetInstance()->bthread_mem_tracker());
        _closure->cntl.Reset();
    }
    ……
    if (_parent->_transfer_large_data_by_brpc && _brpc_request.has_block() &&
        _brpc_request.block().has_column_values() &&
        _brpc_request.ByteSizeLong() > MIN_HTTP_BRPC_SIZE) {
        SCOPED_SWITCH_THREAD_MEM_TRACKER_LIMITER(ExecEnv::GetInstance()->bthread_mem_tracker());
        ……
        _brpc_http_stub->transmit_block_by_http(&_closure->cntl, nullptr, &_closure->result,
                                                _closure);
    } else {
        SCOPED_SWITCH_THREAD_MEM_TRACKER_LIMITER(ExecEnv::GetInstance()->bthread_mem_tracker());
        _closure->cntl.http_request().Clear();
        _brpc_stub->transmit_block(&_closure->cntl, &_brpc_request, &_closure->result, _closure);
    }
```

- In transmit block, the brpc server deserializes the `Request` memory within the server and releases it in `done->Run()`, which removes the latter from the query mem tracker.
```
void PInternalServiceImpl::_transmit_block(google::protobuf::RpcController* cntl_base,
                                           const PTransmitDataParams* request,
                                           PTransmitDataResult* response,
                                           google::protobuf::Closure* done,
                                           const Status& extract_st) {
    ……
    if (extract_st.ok()) {
        SCOPED_ATTACH_TASK(transmit_tracker, ThreadContext::TaskType::QUERY, query_id, finst_id);
        st = _exec_env->vstream_mgr()->transmit_block(request, &done);
    }
    if (done != nullptr) {
        st.to_protobuf(response->mutable_status());
        done->Run();
    }
}
```

#### Reproduce and test
- `USE_JEMALLOC=OFF sh build.sh`
- be.conf add: `tc_enable_aggressive_memory_decommit=true`
- session variables add: 
```
set global exec_mem_limit=285899345920;
set parallel_fragment_exec_instance_num=16;
set enable_vectorized_engine=true;
set batch_size=4096;
set disable_join_reorder=false;
set enable_cost_based_join_reorder=false;
set enable_projection=false;
```
- tpch test case:
```
select
    count(o_orderkey) as c_count
from
    orders right outer join customer on
        c_custkey = o_custkey
        and o_comment not like '%special%requests%';
```

